==Scottish Gaelic==

===Verb===
'''tha'''

#The positive present-tense form of the [[copula]], the verb "to be." It is used to connect a noun to an adjective, pronoun, or verbal noun.
# [[is]], [[are]], [[am]], [[art]]
#*Tha mi pòsda.
#**I'm married.
#*Tha mi à Colbhasa. 
#**I am from Colonsay.
#*Tha mi a' smaoineachadh gu bheil. 
#**(lit.) I am at thinking so.
#* Tha an duine anns an taigh.
#** The man is in the house.
# there is, there are
#* Tha duine anns an taigh.
#** There is a man in the house.
#* Tha daoine anns an taigh.
#** There are men in the house.

